    <main>
        <section id="intro">
            <h3>Introduction</h3>
            <p>TradingBot is a Raspberry Pi-based automated trading solution configured with SmoliTradeOS and many
                other open-source trading tools.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="components">
            <h3>Project Components</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Freqtrade:</strong> A powerful open-source trading bot written in Python, configurable to
                    suit different user needs. Supports machine learning optimization with HyperOpt.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>OctoBot:</strong> Another open-source bot with a user-friendly Web UI, paid services,
                    and LLMs integration capabilities.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>SmolitTrade:</strong> A custom framework that integrates Freqtrade, OctoBot, and other ML/DL algorithms for cohesive automation.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="hardware">
            <h3>Hardware Requirements</h3>
            <p>The TradingBot uses a Raspberry Pi 4 with 8GB RAM, providing ample power while being highly energy
                efficient. Optional display configuration is available at an additional cost.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="access">
            <h3>Access and Updates</h3>
            <p>Access to the bot is available through a Web UI, an app, or Telegram. The bot is designed to automatically install regular updates, including software changes, new strategies, and configurations.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="source-code">
            <h3>Source Code</h3>
            <p>Find all updates and source code in our <a href="https://github.com/user/repo">GitHub repository</a>.</p>
        </section>
